From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
Date: Mon, 2 Mar 2026 12:49:17 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] net/tls: return ENOTSUPP on tls_init()
References: CVE-2024-26584 bsc#1220186
Patch-mainline: never, kABI fix

Disabling TLS config options is a very intrusive operation as the
config options modifies several core kernel structures.

So change 'tls_init()' to return -ENOTSUPP instead to fail loading
of the tls module and issue a warning to alert the user.

Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
Reviewed-by: Petr Pavlu <petr.pavlu@suse.com> # kABI
---
 net/tls/tls_main.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/tls/tls_main.c b/net/tls/tls_main.c
index 2242de51b5430..c43ac8224abc9 100644
--- a/net/tls/tls_main.c
+++ b/net/tls/tls_main.c
@@ -704,6 +704,9 @@ static int tls_init(struct sock *sk)
 	struct tls_context *ctx;
 	int rc = 0;
 
+	pr_warn_once("TLS disabled due to security issues\n");
+	return -ENOTSUPP;
+
 	if (tls_hw_prot(sk))
 		goto out;
 
-- 
2.43.0

